  "local_port": 55074,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Justification for the purpose and conditions of the intended stay?",
  "response": "The purpose and conditions of an intended stay can vary greatly depending on the individual circumstances and requirements of the host country. Here are some common scenarios along with their justifications and conditions:\n\n### Study Abroad\n**Purpose**: To pursue educational programs, degrees, or certifications at an overseas institution.\n**Justification**: Enhance academic qualifications, gain international experience, and receive specialized training not available in the home country.\n**Conditions**:\n- Proof of admission/enrollment in a recognized institution.\n- Evidence of financial means to support tuition fees and living expenses.\n- Valid student visa and compliance with its terms.\n- Health insurance coverage.\n- Regular attendance and satisfactory academic performance.\n\n### Employment\n**Purpose**: To work either temporarily or permanently in the host country.\n**Justification**: Contribute expertise to the host country's workforce, gain international professional experience, or fill a job role where there is a shortage in the host country.\n**Conditions**:\n- Valid work permit/visa.\n- Contract of employment from a recognized employer.\n- Meeting qualification and skill criteria required for the job.\n- Proof of accommodation arrangements.\n- Adherence to local labor laws and standards.\n\n### Tourism\n**Purpose**: To visit for leisure, sightseeing, and experiencing the culture of the host country.\n**Justification**: Promote intercultural understanding, relaxation, and recreational activities.\n**Conditions**:\n- Valid tourist visa.\n- Evidence of sufficient funds to cover stay and return travel expenses.\n- Proof of accommodation arrangements (hotel bookings, etc.).\n- Adherence to the duration of stay as permitted by the visa.\n\n### Medical Treatment\n**Purpose**: To undergo specific medical procedures or treatments.\n**Justification**: Access to specialized medical care not available in the home country.\n**Conditions**:\n- Valid medical visa.\n- Written recommendation from local healthcare professionals.\n- Scheduled appointment or admission confirmation from the host country\u2019s medical facility.\n- Evidence of financial means to cover medical treatments and accommodations.\n\n### Family Reunion\n**Purpose**: To join family members who are residents/citizens in the host country.\n**Justification**: Strengthen family bonds and provide support.\n**Conditions**:\n- Valid family reunion visa.\n- Proof of relationship with the resident/citizen.\n- Evidence of financial means (either self-funding or sponsorship by the family member) to cover living expenses.\n- Compliance with host country\u2019s family reunification policies.\n\n### Business or Investment\n**Purpose**: To explore business opportunities, establish a startup, invest in local ventures, or attend business meetings/conferences.\n**Justification**: Foster economic cooperation, job creation, and market expansion.\n**Conditions**:\n- Valid business visa.\n- Proof of intention and ability to conduct business (such as invitation letters, business plans, or evidence of existing business operations).\n- Financial means to support the business activities and personal expenses.\n- Compliance with local business regulations and taxation laws.\n\n### Diplomatic or Official Missions\n**Purpose**: To represent one\u2019s country in an official capacity.\n**Justification**: Facilitate international relations, negotiate treaties, and participate in diplomatic activities.\n**Conditions**:\n- Valid diplomatic visa.\n- Evidence of official posting and role.\n- Compliance with diplomatic protocols and local laws.\n\nEach scenario requires specific documentation and adherence to the host country's legal conditions to justify the purpose of stay and ensure compliance.",
